<p>"You can take a certain amount of decisions based on that, but at the same time, you don't want to make too many concessions," Andersson said. "It needs to be a great game for the player who plays all the way through. That's the most important part for us, being the story-centric studio as we are."</p><p>Overall, Andersson described this as "a hard balance" to strike for The Great Circle. "You always know that you should worry about that more, but at the same time, you care about the grand scheme of things," he said.</p><p>The Great Circle launched in December 2024 for Xbox Series X|S and PC before coming to PS5 in April 2025. A Nintendo Switch 2 version of the game is coming in 2026, but a release date has not been announced.</p><p>Next up for The Great Circle is the game's new expansion, Order of Giants, which launches on September 4. MachineGames doesn't have any announce upcoming projects, but Lucasfilm has said <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/lucasfilm-says-it-would-be-super-interesting-to-make-more-indiana-jones-games/1100-6528369/" data-ref-id="1100-6528369">it would be "super interesting" to tell more Indiana Jones stories in gaming.</a></p><div data-embed-type="html"><p><i>Click the button below to add GameSpot as a preferred source on Google</i></p></div>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
